gin":25147,"position":0},"title":"Hadith on Hajj: Recommendation to shave head, permission to cut only","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"March 15, 2014","format":false,"excerpt":"Abdullah ibn Umar reported: At the end of the Hajj pilgrimage, the Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cO Allah, have mercy upon those who shaved their heads.\u201d They said, \u201cAnd those who cut their hair short, O Messenger of Allah.\u201d The Prophet said, \u201cO Allah,\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":25505,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2017\/12\/01\/beginning-deeds-yamin-yameen\/","url_meta":{"origin":25147,"position":1},"title":"Hadith on Mindfulness: Beginning actions with the right side","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"December 1, 2017","format":false,"excerpt":"Aisha reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, liked to begin on his right side when putting on his shoes, combing his hair, performing his ablution, and in all of his affairs. Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 168, S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 268 Grade:\u00a0Muttafaqun Alayhi\u00a0(authenticity agreed upon) according to Al-Bukhari and Muslim\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":25293,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2017\/10\/22\/when-the-prophet-forgot-ablution\/","url_meta":{"origin":25147,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Prayer: When the Prophet forgot ablution for prayer","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"October 22, 2017","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Huraira reported: The prayer had been prepared and the rows straightened, then the Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, came out to us. When he stood in his place of prayer, he remembered that he was in a state of ritual impurity (junub). The Prophet said\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":797,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2011\/05\/20\/prophet-business-yahud\/","url_meta":{"origin":25147,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on Trade: The Prophet has business relations with Jews","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"May 20, 2011","format":false,"excerpt":"Aisha reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, passed away while his armor was mortgaged to a Jew for thirty portions of barley. Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 2916, S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 1603 Grade:\u00a0Muttafaqun Alayhi\u00a0(authenticity agreed upon) according to Al-Bukhari and Muslim \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0639\u064e\u0627\u0626\u0650\u0634\u064e\u0629\u064e \u0631\u064e\u0636\u0650\u064a\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652\u0647\u064e\u0627 \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e\u062a\u0652 \u062a\u064f\u0648\u064f\u0641\u0650\u0651\u064a\u064e \u0631\u064e\u0633\u064f\u0648\u0644\u064f \u0627\u0644\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0647\u0650\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},